## Parallel execution (worktrees)

Tack can run each feature in an **isolated git worktree** + branch so multiple agent sessions do not clobber the same working tree. The helper is `project/scripts/tack-worktree.sh` (see `project/docs/sdd.md` ‚Äî **Parallel features**). Configure:

- `tack.worktree.mode`: `<prompt | always | never>` ‚Äî default **`prompt`**: the auto-orchestrator asks before creating a worktree. Use **`always`** to skip the question, **`never`** to keep the legacy single-worktree flow.
- `tack.worktree.naming`: default **`feature/S-XXX-<slug>`** (branch example: `feature/S-001-login`). Alternative: **`feature/<slug>`** (no spec id in the branch name).
- `tack.worktree.base`: `<main | master | develop | detect>` ‚Äî branch to fork from; **`detect`** (default) lets the script pick an existing local branch (`main` ‚Üí `master` ‚Üí current).
- `tack.worktree.dir`: **`.worktrees`** ‚Äî parent directory for linked worktrees (must stay **gitignored**; the script appends `/.` to `.gitignore` on first use).
- `tack.worktree.cleanup`: `<prompt | always | never>` ‚Äî default **`prompt`**: after the pipeline finishes the auto-orchestrator asks whether to delete the feature worktree + branch when it is **safe** (clean tree + branch merged into base + branch matches `feature/*` + worktree under `tack.worktree.dir`). Use **`always`** to skip the question and auto-delete when safe; **`never`** to skip the offer entirely. Protected branches (`main`, `master`, `develop`, `staging`, `release/*`, `hotfix/*`, ‚Ä¶) are **never** deletable by the helper script regardless of this setting ‚Äî that guard lives in `tack-worktree.sh` and is not bypassable.

The directory `.worktrees/` must not be committed. If your repo already uses another location, set `tack.worktree.dir` and ignore that path in `.gitignore`.

## Auto-orchestration routing

- `tack.routing.auto`: `<yes | no>` ‚Äî default **`yes`**: every feature/bug/task is dispatched through `@project/prompts/auto-orchestrator.md` (the active SDD pipeline). Set to **`no`** to keep the passive flow where the human `@`-mentions `@project/prompts/orchestrator.md` manually.

When `tack.routing.auto = no`, agents still read **`TACK.md`** for commands and worktree keys; only the default dispatch path changes.

